theorem Topology.frontier_eq_empty_iff_closure_eq_interior {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier A = (∅ : Set X) ↔ closure A = interior A := by
  constructor
  · intro hFrontier
    -- First, show `closure A ⊆ interior A`.
    have hSub : closure A ⊆ interior A := by
      intro x hxClos
      by_cases hxInt : x ∈ interior A
      · exact hxInt
      ·
        -- Otherwise `x` would lie in the (empty) frontier, a contradiction.
        have hxFront : x ∈ frontier A := And.intro hxClos hxInt
        have : (x : X) ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
          simpa [hFrontier] using hxFront
        cases this
    -- Combine the inclusions to obtain the desired equality.
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm hSub (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ closure A)
  · intro hEq
    exact Topology.frontier_eq_empty_of_closure_eq_interior (A := A) hEq
